children.subject: Personally, I found CS170 to be a little bit more time-consuming, since working on the weekly problem sets on proofs/algorithms requires a little bit more time than the homework/projects in CS188 that do not go into depth as much. CS170, in that sense, is a lot similar to CS70. Personally, I have found CS61C really fast-paced, so that is something to take into account that if you want to take CS170 instead of CS188 you will need to reserve sometime for both 170 and 61C. A lighter CS class you can take is perhaps CS160.

history.content: Hello everyone, I need some recommendations related to technical electives. I am planning to take CS 61C, CS 188, and I need one more lighter technical elective. Besides that, I also have a personal project to complete in the fall and I don't want more pressure in the schedule. Sorry for last-minute recommendation and thank you in advance. Also, I am debating whether I should take 170 or 188. Any suggestions will be appreciated.
history.subject: Recommendations
